All you need is love 🤎 

To my baby girl thank you for completing our family, I can’t wait to do all the things with you 🩷 

Brué is already taking his big brother's duties seriously. He’s such a good helper and loves giving sissy kisses. I can’t wait for when they can play together.  We had no issues with him welcoming her home. 

I have reclaimed my time and stopped pumping milk because of that I’ve been getting more sleep and things are easier the second time around. I produce so much milk with Brué (oversupply I was always engorged, always in pain and nothing seemed to slow down my production. (Maybe pcos and high prolactin) Not sure?!

My anxiety was at an all-time high and looking back I was unhappy, and irritated because of it but I kept doing it because I thought I needed to. I still have a deep freezer full of milk from Brué. I should have gone into business selling milk bricks. 

My business name would have been The Real Muscle Milk 😂🤣 I hear my fellow bodybuilders are in need of mother milk 📲 DM and I'll be your supplier 🤣 all jokes but $8 an oz is tempting. 

#family #breastfeeding #mothersmilk #houstonblogger #breastfeedingmama #motheroftwo #houstoninfluencer #personaltrainer #katypersonaltrainer #fitmom #pcospregnancy #familyportraits #blackfamily

Finally, recognized my reflection in the mirror.  Over a week postpartum and recovering better than expected at my big age, and second child. 🫶🏾🎉

My days are good some nights are better than others. We are managing the best we can as a family of four.  @wahhabc is always are MVP doing all the things and more. 

During the harder moments and big feelings, I’m reminded it won't be like this for long. 

Thank you for checking on us. ❤️‍🩹

38 weeks +1 
Baby girl is around 6 lbs and momma is up 30 lbs which is a big drop from my first pregnancy. I gained a total of 50lbs and he was born 40+6 days at 7lb 9oz

I’m currently 1cm dilated and I’m so ecstatic about it because it lets me know progress is happening with a step closer to welcoming our baby girl home. 

Although I’m so over being pregnant these last few weeks I can’t help but get emotional 🥹 how grateful I am to carry my second child full-term. 

I spent years hating my body disliking myself because I felt my body was broken and working against me as we struggled with infertility and PCOS. 

This was extremely challenging for me, because over the years during my bodybuilding times, I had so much confidence in my body’s abilities to do what I wanted it to do. 

There's a blessing in every struggle so today I'm humbled and grateful for this journey because life is so sweet with my babies B&B 
Brué&B***n 💗🩵
@wahhabc @bruecarter 

#pregnancy #pcospregnancy #love #bunintheoven #momoftwo #houstoninfluencer #mommyblogger #thisislove

We’ll be 9 months pregnant on Thursday! 🤯 How did we get here so fast? 

The second time around hits differently. I GOT THIS until I don’t 🤣😅 those contractions baby don’t play. 

I just remember the first time I got labor contractions It never stopped and it was back to back I’m talking about no warmup 1-3 min apart. 

I’m curious as to what this journey will look like. I feel more prepared knowing I’ve gone through this before.
